2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper deals with modeling contacts and dynamics of interactions, which are relevant to robotics. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper mentions trajectory optimization, which is a common machine learning technique. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is likely as the paper deals with recognizing positions and timing of contacts, which can be seen as an AI problem. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with reconstructing 3D motion, which is relevant to computer graphics.
